  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study is to evaluate the soluble biomarker syndecan-1 (sSdc1) taken from
      venous blood of patients with infectious intestinal diseases such as Clostridium
      difficile-associated colitis, bacterial colitis, Norovirus enteritis and Crohn´s disease or
      ulcerative colitis. The level of sSdc1 will be compared with disease activity in patients
      with active inflammation and with disease in remission. Secondary objectives were the
      assessment of correlation of the above-mentioned factors with the CRP value. Subjects will be
      volunteers. Blood will be taken as part of the routine clinical work-up after the written
      agreement blood and sSdc1-level will be assessed using a human-specific sSdc1 ELISA assay. In
      addition, the subjects are asked to answer a short questionnaire. The study is designed as a
      prospective, comparative cohort study.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
